				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\varvec{s}_i\in {\mathcal {S}}({\mathcal {Y}})$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M452"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="bold-italic">s</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>&#x02208;</mml:mo><mml:mi mathvariant="script">S</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi mathvariant="script">Y</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="11538_2018_415_Article_IEq204.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> and, with high enough probability, would be silent to all <inline-formula id="IEq205"><alternatives><tex-math id="M453">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
