				\begin{document}$$\theta $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M710"><mml:mi>&#x003b8;</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="11538_2018_415_Article_IEq317.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> sufficiently close to the highest feasible values specified in Theorems <xref ref-type="sec" rid="FPar2">1</xref> and <xref ref-type="sec" rid="FPar6">2</xref>.</p><p id="Par78">In addition to rather general model of neuronal behavior, another major theoretical assumption of our work was the presumption that stimuli informational content is drawn from an equidistribution in a unit ball <inline-formula id="IEq318"><alternatives><tex-math id="M711">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
